On March 14, 2022, the President signed two bills into law. The first one, H.R. 3665, designates the medical center of the Department of Veterans Affairs in San Diego, California, as the Jennifer Moreno Department of Veterans Affairs Medical Center. It also supports the designation of a component of the medical center in honor of Kathleen Bruyere. The second bill, S. 854, known as the "Methamphetamine Response Act of 2021," designates methamphetamine as an emerging drug threat. It also requires the Office of National Drug Control Policy to develop and implement a national response plan specific to methamphetamine. The bills received support from various representatives and senators, including Mike Levin, Juan Vargas, Sara Jacobs, Darrell Issa, Scott Peters, Julia Brownley, John Curtis, Diana Harshbarger, Cindy Axne, Josh Harder, Dianne Feinstein, and Chuck Grassley.